<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US"> <!--The language is declared with the lang attribute.  -->
<head>
	<title>Attributes</title>
</head>
<body> 


<!-- You can add attributes in tags.  -->

<!-- href for/to add url links. -->
<a href="https://www.cubeacloud.com">This is a link</a>

<!-- src for/to internal source links & The alt attribute specifies an alternative text to be used, if an image cannot be displayed.-->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="flower">

<!-- if we want to align a code in center how we do it?. -->
<p align="center">simple its done by adding *align="center*</p>




<!-- A simple tag. -->
<p>A simple paragraph</p>

<!-- using style attribute tag. -->
<p style="color:red">color red</p>



<!-- A paragraph with attribute. -->
<p align="center">See its simple to a</p>




<!-- we can go left & right too, with align attribute. -->
<p align="right">A aligned paragraph on right side</p>
<p align="left">A aligned paragraph on left side</p>




<!-- Hr tag is used for horizontal line. -->
<p>Some Text</p>
<hr>
<p>Some Text</p>



<!-- now we will add an width attribute in hr tag. -->
<p>A width attribute with the value of pixels</p>
<hr width="70px">
<hr width="70%">
<p>You can also use percentage in width attribute</p>




<!-- Now its time to learn text formatting elements. -->


<!-- Down below are the example on how you can make text bold, strong, italic e.t.c-->
<p>A normal paragraph</p>
<p><small>A paragraph with small text</small></p>
<p><big>A paragraph with big text</big></p>
<p><b>A paragraph with bold text</b></p>
<p><i>A paragraph with italic text</i></p>
<p><strong>A paragraph with strong text</strong></p>
<p><sub>A paragraph with subscripted text</sub></p>
<p><ins>A paragraph with inserted text</ins></p>
<p><sup>A paragraph with superscripted text</sup></p>
<p><del>A paragraph with deleted text</del></p>


</body>
</html>
